messages.messageBody:
Schuyler,

She hasn't because they are usually spoken for by then. She has considered it and will maybe try this year. Several of my children go to historical reenactments as 1850's reenactors and she shears sheep by hand in full prairie dress (can I send a pic to this group? I really need to start a new blog) usually people are speaking for the fleece of the lambs as it falls off the sheep!
Btw we enjoyed the great slide show on your blog.
Julie
mom to the darlin' dozen.(Hoping we will be changing this to the bakers dozen in about 7 months!) Grandma to Paul and Ryne and soon to be born Peyten!



[Non-text portions of this message have been removed]
